### 📊 Student Marks Prediction using Machine Learning

### 📝 Project Overview

This project is a Student Marks Predictor that utilizes machine learning to forecast student performance based on input features like study hours. The trained model is saved as Student_mark_predictor_model.pkl and can be used to make real-time predictions.

### 🔍 Features

1. Preprocessed dataset with relevant academic features
2. Machine learning model trained and saved as a .pkl file
3. Model evaluation using performance metrics
4. Easy-to-use interface for making predictions

### 🛠️ Technologies Used

1. Python for development
2. Scikit-Learn for machine learning
3. Pandas, NumPy for data handling
4. Matplotlib, Seaborn for data visualization
5. Flask/Streamlit (optional) for web-based interaction

### 📁 Dataset

The dataset used for training includes features such as study hours. The model was trained using regression techniques to achieve accurate predictions.

### 📈 Model Performance

The model was evaluated using Mean Absolute Error (MAE), R² Score, and other metrics to ensure reliable predictions. Detailed evaluation results are included in the repository.

### 🤝 Contributions

Feel free to fork this repository, improve the model, and submit pull requests.

